@prefix ex: <https://vocab.cfaa.eus/broaching/> .
ex:BloqueBusqueda ex:textoExtracto "With block search, it is possible to recover the program history up to a particular block in such way that if program execution is resumed at that block, it will do so with the same conditions as if it were executed from the beginning." ;
    a ex:ModoOperacion ;
    ex:identificador "block search" .

ex:BusquedaBloqueAutomatica ex:textoExtracto "The automatic block search may be used to recover the program history up to the block where the previous execution was canceled. The CNC remembers the block where interruption was canceled, thus not being necessary to set the stop block." ;
    a ex:ModoOperacion ;
    ex:identificador "automatic block search" .

ex:BusquedaBloqueManual ex:textoExtracto "The manual block search may be used to recover the program history up to a particular block of the program or of the subroutine, set by the operator." ;
    a ex:ModoOperacion ;
    ex:identificador "manual block search" .

ex:BusquedaBloque ex:textoExtracto "Executing block search. 1 Selecting the type of search: automatic or manual. 2 Selecting the stop block. In the automatic block search, there is no need to select the stop block; by default, the CNC runs the search up to the block where the program was interrupted. 3 Selecting the starting block for the search. If the first block is not selected, the block search starts at the beginning of the program. 4 Press the [CYCLE START] key to start the block search. 5 Depending on how the treatment of functions M, H, F, S is configured, it may be necessary to decide which ones are sent out to the PLC. 6 Reposition the axes to the point to resume execution. 7 Tool inspection may be accessed to change the machining conditions. 8 Press [START] to execute the program." ;
    a ex:TareaMantenimiento ;
    ex:identificador "Executing block search" .

ex:TeclaCycleStart ex:textoExtracto "Press the [CYCLE START] key to start the block search." ;
    a ex:InterfazUsuario ;
    ex:identificador "[CYCLE START]" .

ex:TeclaStart ex:textoExtracto "Press [START] to execute the program." ;
    a ex:InterfazUsuario ;
    ex:identificador "[START]" .

ex:TeclaStop ex:textoExtracto "Repositioning may be interrupted (using the [STOP] key) to select other axes." ;
    a ex:InterfazUsuario ;
    ex:identificador "[STOP]" .

ex:SistemaCNC ex:textoExtracto "The CNC remembers the block where interruption was canceled" ;
    a ex:Maquina ;
    ex:identificador "CNC" .

ex:Eje ex:textoExtracto "Reposition the axes to the point to resume execution." ;
    a ex:ComponenteMecanico ;
    ex:identificador "axes" .

ex:RuedaManual ex:textoExtracto "Jog the axes with the handwheels or with the JOG keys." ;
    a ex:ComponenteMecanico ;
    ex:identificador "handwheels" .

ex:TeclasJOG ex:textoExtracto "Jog the axes with the handwheels or with the JOG keys." ;
    a ex:InterfazUsuario ;
    ex:identificador "JOG keys" .

ex:PuntoReposicionFin ex:textoExtracto "The movement is limited by the repositioning end point and the corresponding software limit." ;
    a ex:Parametro ;
    ex:identificador "repositioning end point" .

ex:LimiteSoftware ex:textoExtracto "The movement is limited by the repositioning end point and the corresponding software limit." ;
    a ex:Parametro ;
    ex:identificador "software limit" .

ex:InspeccionHerramienta ex:textoExtracto "Tool inspection may be accessed to change the machining conditions." ;
    a ex:TareaMantenimiento ;
    ex:identificador "Tool inspection" .